Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Maps of Japan can be seen at http://mapsof.net/uploads/static-maps/cities_of_japan_map.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4506455,156.

The pending shortage of vaccine may be due to the offer of free vaccination to 900 workers at Kansai International Airport; see: Measles update (46): Japan (OS) Kansai airport 20160909.4478118.

The common theme running through all the measles outbreak reports is the importance of vaccination. Two doses are required for protection. After one dose of measles vaccine, 85 per cent of children 9 months of age and 95 per cent over 12 months of age are immune. Nearly all of those who do not develop immunity after a single dose develop it after a 2nd dose. - Mod.LK]
